member.name: M:RoutesModule.RoutesVars.SIDIsBillable(RoutesModule.RoutesVars.SID@,System.DateTime,System.DateTime)
member.summary: This function will quickly determine whether or not an SID is billable based on the SID's "Start Date" and/or "End Date" and/or "Last Bill Date" and the start and end dates of the billing period for which the SID is being examined.
member.returns: The function will return TRUE if the SID is billable or FALSE if it is not.
member.remarks: The logic employed in this function assumes that the tests are conducted in a specific order. This is critical since certain things may be assumed based on exclusion. Although certain other information about the SID can be deduced about the SID, such as whether or not it is a Restart, we refrain from doing so within this function because that additional information cannot always be known and we do not want to detract from the functions stated purpose which is simply to classify an SID as billable or not.
